I implemented something like this to show the diff of dicts/lists when there is inequality, this is useful to have in the framework.

```
from datadiff import diff
from expects import equal


class equal_or_diff(equal):

    def _failure_message(self, subject, *args):
        return str(diff(self._expected, subject))
```

This does introduce a dependency, so I am not sure that this enhancement is acceptable.

