Hello everyone, especially @miguelgrinberg !

Is there a way to control SocketIO app via web api. To be more precise i want use web api (Flask) to control SocketIO handlers. For example, i want have WebApi method, that can setup new message handler for SocketIO app.

This is sketch of this service, but this obviously doesn't work as i expected.

```
import socketio
import eventlet.wsgi
from flask import Flask, jsonify, abort, make_response, request

app = Flask(__name__)
sio = socketio.Server()

@app.route('/')
def index():
    return 'Hello folks! This is mock SocketIO server for testing.'

@app.route('/set_sio_handler', methods=['POST'])
def set_sio_handler():
    @sio.on('commands')
    def message_handler(sid, msg):
        if msg['data']['command'] == request.json['command']:
            response_msg = {'handler': msg['handler'],
                            'data': {'result':   request.json['result']}}
            sio.emit('commands', response_msg)

if __name__ == '__main__':
    mid = socketio.Middleware(sio, app)
    eventlet.wsgi.server(eventlet.listen(('127.0.0.1', 1234)), mid)
```

Are there any suggestions how to do this?

Nice library, however I'm encountering some strangeness with IE10.  

If I choose the same file after an attempt at uploading, my file model is a blank string.  A 3rd attempt and it's an empty array, according to VS.

